    "description": "Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates has an exciting opening for a Senior Teacher at our Bhubaneswar office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates:\nOsmania University Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n• Create curriculum-aligned learning materials and assessments\n• Participate in teacher training and professional development programs\n• Collaborate with faculty on curriculum development initiatives\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Conduct doubt-clearing sessions and remedial classes for weak students\n• Conduct parent-teacher meetings and update parents on student performance\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in MS Office\n• Proficiency in Research Skills\n• Proficiency in Child Psychology\n• Proficiency in Mentoring\n• Proficiency in E-learning\n• Proficiency in Special Education\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Osmania University Asia Pacific Associates!",
